<dl id="n26270b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26270b">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26270b"> 270(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Vesta &amp; Janus</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Household worship]</font>&mdash;<mark>Janus</mark>, the god of the door, comes undoubtedly first, though unfortunately we know but little of his worship in the household, except that it was the concern of the men. To the women is committed the worship of the &ldquo;blazing hearth&rdquo;, <mark>Vesta</mark>, the natural centre of the family life <small> &ldquo;ROMAN RELIGION&rdquo; <a name="EBRR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRR"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 578</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
